title: Solitary Tree in the Fleurieu Peninsula, South Australia
text:
Solitary Tree in the Fleurieu Peninsula, South Australia 
Camera NIKON D300S Aperture f/5 Exposure Time 1/4000 
South Australia is often the forgotten state in Australia. It is often overshadowed by the states in the east and the giant Western Australia. It is too bad because there is a lot of great stuff to see in South Australia. 
The Fleurieu Peninsula is a great wine producing region and as you can see in the photo, it is a landscape very different from much of Australia. Get My FREE 100 Page Travel Photography eBook!
